      Each path is the SVG `d` data copied verbatim from the source, prefixed with `F1`
      so Avalonia uses the NonZero fill rule (SVG's default) — several glyphs (gear, copy,
      info, warning…) rely on it to punch their holes correctly. Referenced as
      PathIcon Data="{StaticResource IconName}"; a PathIcon fills with its Foreground, which
      inherits the ambient text colour, so icons recolour with the theme automatically.
    -->

